+---
+date: "2026-06-11"
+status: done
+implements: [FR-E83]
+tags: [engine, recovery, cli, journal]
+related_tasks:
+  - 2026/05/durable-run-lifecycle-replay.md
+---
+# engine: Runs doctor journal health checker
+
+## Goal
+
+Add a `runs doctor` CLI command that audits one run's durability artifacts,
+reports every detected problem, and applies only safe mechanical repairs.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+`journal.jsonl` is the only durable run recovery record. Crashes, manual edits,
+and bugs can leave a run degraded: torn tail lines, semantic journal errors,
+missing or orphaned node directories, and stale workflow locks. Operators need a
+single non-interactive command that diagnoses these cases and safely repairs the
+two mechanical cases that require no semantic guessing.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` owns journal parsing and replay. It already
+  tolerates a malformed partial final line and deduplicates event IDs.
+- `src/state/state.ts` owns run and node path helpers.
+- `src/state/lock.ts` owns `<workflowDir>/runs/.lock` path construction,
+  parsing, and live-process checks.
+- `src/cli.ts` routes top-level subcommands and keeps argument parsing local.
+- No command currently diagnoses a run directory without resuming the engine.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Reuse `replayRunJournal()` as the single replay truth. Do not write a second
+  state replayer.
+- Reuse `getRunDir()`, `getNodeDir()`, `getJournalPath()`,
+  `defaultLockPath()`, and `readLockInfo()` instead of duplicating layout or
+  lock knowledge.
+- No dependencies.
+- Report all findings, not just the first.
+- `--repair` may remove only a torn final journal line and a stale lock for the
+  target run.
+- Refuse repairs when the run is live or when journal errors go beyond the
+  torn final line.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] `flowai-workflow runs doctor --workflow <dir> --run <runId>` reports
+      journal integrity, replay invariant, filesystem, and stale-lock findings
+      grouped by severity, returning 0 without errors and 1 with errors.
+      Tuple: FR-E83; Test `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::FR-E83 clean run exits ok` +
+      related doctor diagnosis tests; Evidence `deno task check`.
+- [x] `--repair` backs up and atomically rewrites a journal with only a torn
+      final line, preserves `journal.jsonl.bak`, removes a stale lock for the
+      target run, and refuses live locks or non-tail journal errors without
+      modifying files. Tuple: FR-E83; Test
+      `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::FR-E83 repair torn final line round trip`
+      and repair refusal tests; Evidence `deno task check`.
+- [x] `--json` emits a machine-readable findings list with `severity`, `code`,
+      `message`, and `evidence_path`. Tuple: FR-E83; Test
+      `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::FR-E83 json output shape`; Evidence
+      `deno task check`.
+- [x] CLI help lists `runs doctor`. Tuple: FR-E83; Test
+      `src/cli_test.ts::FR-E83 help mentions runs doctor`; Evidence
+      `deno task check`.
+- [x] Add `FR-E83` to engine SRS with an `**Acceptance criteria:**` block.
+      Tuple: FR-E83; Test
+      `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md::FR-E83`; Evidence
+      `deno task check`.
+- [x] Full project gate passes. Tuple: FR-E83; Test `deno task check`; Evidence
+      `deno task check`.
+
+## Solution
+
+### Selected Variant
+
+Architecturally-correct implementation: add a dedicated doctor module under
+`src/state/` and keep `src/cli.ts` as a thin argument/output adapter.
+
+Rationale: a direct `cli.ts` implementation is faster but would mix diagnosis,
+repair, and formatting in the entry point. A broader diagnostics framework is
+not justified by a one-run command. The state-level module matches the existing
+ownership of journals, paths, and locks while staying narrowly scoped.
+
+### Files to Create or Modify
+
+- `src/state/run-doctor.ts`
+  - Export diagnosis and repair functions plus finding/result types.
+  - Parse journal lines only for integrity checks; delegate state rebuilding to
+    `replayRunJournal()`.
+  - Load workflow config and build `PhaseRegistry` so phased node directory
+    checks use the same helper path semantics as the engine.
+  - Compare journal-declared node IDs and node-directory declarations against
+    workflow config and run-dir filesystem entries.
+  - Detect events after terminal run events, undeclared-node lifecycle events,
+    attempt start/completion mismatches keyed by `node_id` + `iteration`, and
+    total-cost divergence.
+  - Detect stale target-run locks using `defaultLockPath()` and
+    `readLockInfo()`.
+  - Apply repair only after a preflight confirms no live target-run lock and no
+    journal errors beyond a torn final line.
+  - Return repair actions in the result so human and JSON output both report
+    every modification.
+- `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts`
+  - Build fabricated workflow/run directories and journal records.
+  - Cover clean, torn final line, mid-file garbage, unknown kind, terminal-tail
+    events, cost divergence, orphan directory, missing declared directory,
+    stale lock, repair success/refusals, and JSON shape.
+- `src/cli.ts`
+  - Add `runs doctor` routing and parser following existing local parsing
+    style.
+  - Print grouped human report or JSON findings.
+  - Exit 0 when no `ERROR` finding exists, else 1.
+  - Include `runs doctor` in `printUsage()`.
+- `src/cli_test.ts`
+  - Assert help text mentions `runs doctor`.
+- `documents/requirements-engine.md`
+  - Add `FR-E83` index entry pointing to `01-execution-model`.
+- `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md`
+  - Add durability/recovery requirement section for `runs doctor`.
+- `documents/design-engine/02-engine-modules-flow.md`
+  - Mention the new `runs doctor` CLI subcommand and state module ownership if
+    existing CLI/module descriptions become stale.
+- `documents/index.md`
+  - Register the new FR row.
+
+### Implementation Approach
+
+1. RED: add run-doctor unit tests for diagnosis and repair behavior.
+2. GREEN: implement `src/state/run-doctor.ts` with pure diagnosis/repair logic.
+3. RED/GREEN: add a CLI help test and wire `runs doctor` dispatch.
+4. REFACTOR: tighten finding codes, output grouping, and shared fixtures.
+5. CHECK: run focused tests, then `deno task check`.
+
+### Error Handling Strategy
+
+- Missing journal is an `ERROR` finding and prevents repair.
+- Unparsable final non-newline line is a `WARNING`; unparsable non-final line is
+  an `ERROR`.
+- Unknown event kinds, replay failures, non-monotonic sequence numbers,
+  terminal-tail events, undeclared lifecycle events, unmatched attempts, and
+  cost divergence are `ERROR` findings.
+- Duplicate `event_id`, torn final line, orphan/missing directories, and stale
+  lock are `WARNING` findings unless the task states otherwise.
+- Repair refuses before modifying anything when a live target-run lock exists
+  or when any journal `ERROR` exists.
+
+### Verification Commands
+
+- `deno task test -- run-doctor_test`
+- `deno task test -- cli_test`
+- `deno task check`
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- Multi-run batch diagnosis remains out of scope.
+
+## Review
+
+Verdict: Approve.
+
+Findings: none.
+
+Evidence:
+
+- `deno task test -- run-doctor_test` passed: 1035 passed, 0 failed.
+- `deno task check` passed: full check, 1035 passed, 0 failed.
